## Why This Is Asked

Introduces a practical policy gate that enforces manifest hygiene early in CI, ensuring traceability and consistency across deployments.

## Key Concepts

- YAML manifest traversal and metadata fields
- Distinguishing annotations vs labels and required keys
- Lightweight Node.js validator using js-yaml
- Integrating validator into GitHub Actions as a PR gate

## Code Example

```javascript
const fs = require('fs');
const yaml = require('js-yaml');
function valid(manifest) {
  const m = yaml.load(fs.readFileSync(manifest, 'utf8'));
  const meta = m?.metadata || {};
  const ann = meta.annotations || {};
  const lab = meta.labels || {};
  return ann['app.kubernetes.io/managed-by'] === 'ci-tool' && lab.app && lab.version;
}
module.exports = { valid };
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you extend the validator to report which manifests fail and why?
- How would you adapt the workflow to run in parallel across multiple directories?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests the ability to craft a concrete, beginner-friendly CI gate that enforces per-container resource budgeting and a basic security posture—practical patterns seen in production.

## Key Concepts

- Kubernetes manifest traversal
- GitHub Actions CI gates
- resources.requests/limits
- securityContext basics (readOnlyRootFilesystem, allowPrivilegeEscalation)

## Code Example

```javascript
// Node.js pseudo-check using js-yaml
const fs = require('fs');
const yaml = require('js-yaml');
const path = './manifests';
for (const f of fs.readdirSync(path)) {
  if (!f.endsWith('.yaml')) continue;
  const doc = yaml.load(fs.readFileSync(path + '/' + f, 'utf8'));
  const containers = (doc?.spec?.template?.spec?.containers) || [];
  for (const c of containers) {
    if (!c.resources?.requests || !c.resources?.limits) fail();
    if (c.securityContext?.readOnlyRootFilesystem !== true) fail();
    if (c.securityContext?.allowPrivilegeEscalation !== false) fail();
  }
}
``` 

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you handle multi-namespace repos?
- How would you surface results in PR checks?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical security integration at the API gateway, including key management and CI validation.

## Key Concepts
- API gateway policies
- HMAC-SHA256 signing
- Idempotency keys
- Secrets management and rotation
- CI validation

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo Kong-like middleware for signing validation
const crypto = require('crypto');

function verify(req, secret) {
  const id = req.headers['x-idempotency-key'];
  const sig = req.headers['x-signature'];
  const base = req.method + req.path + JSON.stringify(req.body) + req.headers['x-timestamp'];
  const calc = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret).update(base).digest('hex');
  return id && sig && calc === sig;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test rotation without downtime?
- How handle clock skew between client and gateway?

