## Why This Is Asked
This question tests applying basic IaC security checks to Terraform in cloud contexts, ensuring encryption, least privilege, and network exposure are validated before deployment.

## Key Concepts
- IaC scanning with tfsec/checkov
- S3 default encryption (AES256/KMS)
- IAM least privilege
- RDS publicly accessible flag
- Local vs CI validation

## Code Example
```hcl
# Failing: S3 without encryption
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "bad" {
  bucket = "example-bucket"
}
```
```hcl
# Passing: S3 with encryption
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "good" {
  bucket = "example-bucket"
  server_side_encryption_configuration {
    rule {
      apply_server_side_encryption_by_default {
        sse_algorithm = "AES256"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
```hcl
# Failing: wildcard IAM actions
resource "aws_iam_role_policy" "bad" {
  name = "perm"
  role = aws_iam_role.app.name
  policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17",
    Statement = [{ Action = "*", Effect = "Allow", Resource = "*" }]
  })
}
```
```hcl
# Passing: least-privilege IAM policy
resource "aws_iam_role_policy" "good" {
  name = "least"
  role = aws_iam_role.app.name
  policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17",
    Statement = [{ Action = ["ec2:DescribeInstances"], Effect = "Allow", Resource = "*" }]
  })
}
```
```hcl
# Failing: RDS publicly accessible
resource "aws_db_instance" "db" {
  allocated_storage = 20
  publicly_accessible = true
  engine = "mysql"
  # ...
}
```
```hcl
# Passing: RDS not publicly accessible
resource "aws_db_instance" "db" {
  allocated_storage = 20
  publicly_accessible = false
  engine = "mysql"
  # ...
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle account-wide exceptions?
- How to run checks locally vs in CI for multi-account repos?

